node.text: We got a JUICY one for y'all today! You asked how I deal with drama, so I'm getting honest about how to rise above the petty stuff and focus on what's good. Let me know in the comments how you deal when things get dramatic 🎭

node.text: Let me start by saying, I didn’t know how much work went into creating an app and platform! @frst.place Almost a year of time spent into this, and filming hundreds of workouts over and over to make sure it was optimal and it’s finally all come together. 🥲 Fitness became my crutch through any hard time and I realized how important it was to my well being. I wanted to build a community of real people who go through real things, but wanted to finally put themselves first. You are not alone in this journey!! Thank you to some of you for being very patient… this is just the beginning 🥰 @frst.place

node.text: There were way too many questions for one episode, so I'm back to answer more. Today we're talking about some passion projects I've been working very hard on behind the scenes. node.text: We are back with @BeautyByMariama to add onto the ponytail from last week by styling my baby hairs. It's a trend, I'm trying to do my part, get over it. How do you style your baby hairs? When are they extra and when are they just right? We do our best to answer all these questions and more. Special guest appearance by @JodieWoods with a judgement on the final look.
